string is a data type that sequence of charecters enclosed with single quote ('') or double quotes ("").
example:
   str1 = "sainath reddy"
   str2 = 'sainath'


Every data type has inbuilt function in python.

In same way string has some in built function.
inbuilt functions are

         1. case conversion function 
                 upper()      - that convert text to upper case (sainath - SAINATH)
                 lower()      - convert string to lower case (SAINATH -sainath)
                 title()      - convert first letter of every word to upper case (sainath reddy - Sainath Reddy)
                capitalize()  - capital only first letter of the string (sainath reddy - Sainath reddy)
                swapcase()    - make word upper and lower and wise versa. (sainath - SaInAtH)
         2. searching and replacing
                   find ()     - find the index of that letter ("hello".find(e)) = 1
                  rfind ()     - find the index of last occurancy ("banana".rfind(a)) = 5
                  index ()     - same as find but shows error if not found
                replace ()     - used to replace the string ("sainath reddu".replace ('reddu', 'reddy')) = sainath reddy
         3. checking content
                startswith()   -  if strings start given text then it prints true or false
                  endswith()   -  if string ends with given text theen it prints true or false
                   isdigit()   -  if srting contains all charecters are numbers so prints true, if not print false
                   isalpha()   -  checks if all are alphsbits in string then print true if not false
                   islower()   -  checks string is lower case, if yes print true if not prints false
                   istitle()   -  first letter of every word in string starts with capital, then prints true if not false
         4. spliting and joining 
                   split()     - splits strings into list
                  rsplit()     - splits strings from right
                    join()     - joins lists into strings
              splitlines()     - splits by newlines
         5. trimming
              strip()          - removes space froom both ends
              lstrip()         - removes space from left
              rstrip()         - removes space from right
         
remembering tip : CSCSP (C FOR CASE CONVENTION)
                        (S FOR Search and replace)
                        (c for checking content)
                        (s for splitting and joining)
                        (trimming used to remove space)

